# Implementation Plan - Fix Production Build Error

## Goal
Resolve the runtime error `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'createContext')` in the production build caused by incorrect chunk splitting of core dependencies.

## Proposed Changes

### [Root] [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/dgper/Proyectos/ZeroCode/vite.config.ts)
- Revert the separation of `vendor-react` and `vendor-ui`.
- Consolidate React, React-DOM, React-Router, Framer Motion, and Lucide React into a single `vendor` chunk.
- Keep only truly massive and independent libraries like `firebase`, `pdf`, and `charts` in separate chunks.

### [Sub-Apps] [apps/reformas/vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/dgper/Proyectos/ZeroCode/apps/reformas/vite.config.ts) & [apps/zerodelay/vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/dgper/Proyectos/ZeroCode/apps/zerodelay/vite.config.ts)
- Apply the same consolidation strategy to ensure library consistency.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` and then `npx vite preview` (or check the firebase hosting if deployed) to verify the fix.
- Ensure no console errors occur on boot.
